      name: 'Can you put hot pans on quartz countertops?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Quartz is heat-resistant but not heat-proof. Temperatures above 300 degrees Fahrenheit can damage the resin binders in quartz, potentially causing discoloration or cracking. Always use trivets or hot pads under hot cookware. Granite handles heat better since it is a natural stone without resin, but using trivets is still recommended for both materials.' },
    },
